						               													<description>Splat! Oh no! Granny Smyth's pearl necklace has snapped &amp;ndash; and now all the precious pearls are lying in the mud where the pigs wallow. The pigs immediately charge out to get as many pearls as possible. Help them by finding the right pearls as quickly as you can and placing them in your trough. Be the first to show off the perfect string of pearls!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Aim of the game:&amp;#10;The aim is to be the first to find the pearls that match the face-up pearl cards and get the most points. This means turning over the mud tiles as fast as you can.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game consists of several rounds. One round is always played as follows:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Rooting (all pigs at the same time!)&amp;#10;     Claiming the pearls&amp;#10;     Checking the claim and awarding the pearl card&amp;#10;     Preparing for the next round&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The end of the game:&amp;#10;The game ends when there are not enough pearl cards left to make the row back up to three. Each player now counts up the points for all the pearl cards they have collected. The player with the most points is the winner. If more than one player scores the highest total, they are joint winners.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
